<p>I'm using xjc (jaxb2-maven-plugin) to generate my POJOs from several XSD files.  Not surprisingly, there are class conflicts if I put all my generated files into one package.  By default xjc will use the namespace as a package name.</p>  <p>Ex: </p>  <pre><code>namespace: "https://analysiscenter.domain.com/schema/4.0/sandboxlist" becomes package: https.analysiscenter_domain_com.schema._4_0.sandboxlist </code></pre>  <p>I realize that I can use xjc:bindings to specify individually which namespace becomes which package, but that becomes quite tedious.  Is there any way to specify rules or regexs for the bindings for all xsds?</p>  <p>Ex: namespace .<em>/schema/(.</em>)/(.*) becomes package: myDefaultPackage.$1.$2</p>  <p>Ex something like the following: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;jaxb:bindings schemaLocation="*.xsd" node="/xsd:schema[@value=.*/schema/(.*)/(.*)"&gt;     &lt;jaxb:schemaBindings&gt;         &lt;jaxb:package name="com.domain.$1.$2"/&gt;     &lt;/jaxb:schemaBindings&gt; &lt;/jaxb:bindings&gt; </code></pre>